# Pre-Productive Project

- This project is still pre-productivo.
- By default, prioritize clean domain design, simple APIs, and code clarity over backward compatibility.
- Do not preserve legacy fields, deprecated payloads, transitional adapters, or compatibility shims unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- When a cleaner breaking change is available, prefer the breaking change.
- Prefer removing stale patterns instead of supporting both old and new approaches in parallel.
- Migrations may assume internal schemas can be cleaned up aggressively, as long as the current codebase stays consistent.
- If the user later says the project is already productivo, stop applying this rule.
